abstract: Fliers from the airline saying employees were better off spending on video games and drinks drew backlash on social media amid a push to unionize.
snippet: Fliers from the airline saying employees were better off spending on video games and drinks drew backlash on social media amid a push to unionize.
lead_paragraph: Delta Air Lines is facing backlash for suggesting to employees that it would be more “fun” to spend their money on new video games or rounds of drinks than on union dues.

abstract: Frances Fox Piven has become the intellectual guru of activist progressives. But not everyone is ready to storm the barricades with her.
snippet: Frances Fox Piven has become the intellectual guru of activist progressives. But not everyone is ready to storm the barricades with her.
lead_paragraph: On a recent afternoon, a crowd had gathered in the auditorium of the People’s Forum, a new event space in Midtown Manhattan. There was a picture of Lenin tacked on the wall, a shelf of books about Che Guevara and a cafe serving avocado toast. The young true believers and rickety old militants in attendance were learning history and strategy from Frances Fox Piven, a distinguished professor of political science at the Graduate Center of the City University of New York.

headline_main: This 86-Year-Old Radical May Save (or Sink) the Democrats
headline_print_headline: The Unlikely Revival of a ’60s Radical

abstract: The president seems eager to force the hand of Democrats who are investigating him as if they were conducting an impeachment inquiry without actually calling it that.
snippet: The president seems eager to force the hand of Democrats who are investigating him as if they were conducting an impeachment inquiry without actually calling it that.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the White House and Congress escalate their constitutional showdown, President Trump and his team are essentially trying to call what they see as the Democrats’ bluff. The message: Put up or shut up. Impeach or move on.

abstract: A study of 25 states provides a rare glimpse of the stark disparities between what private insurers and the federal government paid for inpatient and outpatient care.
snippet: A study of 25 states provides a rare glimpse of the stark disparities between what private insurers and the federal government paid for inpatient and outpatient care.
lead_paragraph: In Indiana, a local hospital system, Parkview Health, charged private insurance companies about four times what the federal Medicare program paid for the same care, according to a study of hospital prices in 25 states released on Thursday by the nonprofit RAND Corp.

headline_main: Late Night on Trump’s Business Losses: ‘A One-Man Fyre Festival’

abstract: At a relatively subdued “Make America Great Again” rally on Wednesday night, the president riffed on familiar themes, like the “fake news media” and Hillary Clinton.
snippet: At a relatively subdued “Make America Great Again” rally on Wednesday night, the president riffed on familiar themes, like the “fake news media” and Hillary Clinton.
lead_paragraph: PANAMA CITY BEACH, Fla. — President Trump on Wednesday brought his amped-up roadshow to this spring break playground on the Florida gulf coast, demanding that Democrats stop the “nonsense” of investigating him, mocking Democratic presidential candidates like Joe Biden and Pete Buttigieg, and joking about staying in the White House for another decade.

abstract: Ms. Klobuchar, in a town hall event, called herself a “proven progressive,” while also appealing to Fox’s conservative viewers with her bipartisan record.
snippet: Ms. Klobuchar, in a town hall event, called herself a “proven progressive,” while also appealing to Fox’s conservative viewers with her bipartisan record.
lead_paragraph: Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota defended her presidential candidacy as one that could appeal to both moderate and liberal voters, calling herself a “proven progressive” and casting her record as one of bipartisan accomplishment.

abstract: There is no good reason to put yet another man in the White House.
snippet: There is no good reason to put yet another man in the White House.
lead_paragraph: According to pollsters and political reporters, a dispiriting dynamic has taken hold of the early stages of the Democratic presidential primary: Voters are discounting female candidates as unelectable.
